abstract: A critical guide to productions in New York City, including shows in previews.
snippet: A critical guide to productions in New York City, including shows in previews.
lead_paragraph: Approximate running times are in parentheses. Theaters are in Manhattan unless otherwise noted. Full reviews of current productions, additional listings, showtimes and ticket information are at nytimes.com/theater. A searchable, critical guide to theater is at nytimes.com/events.

abstract: Families of captives that try to raise ransom money for groups like the Islamic State will no longer face the threat of prosecution, officials say.
snippet: Families of captives that try to raise ransom money for groups like the Islamic State will no longer face the threat of prosecution, officials say.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Obama will announce Wednesday that the government will no longer threaten criminal prosecution of the families of American hostages who are held abroad by groups like the Islamic State if they try to pay ransom for the release of their loved ones.

snippet: A critical guide to exhibitions and installations in the New York area.

abstract: The chief executive of Ireland’s soccer association said it was paid after a controversial hand ball by France’s Thierry Henry prevented Ireland from qualifying for the 2010 World Cup.
snippet: The chief executive of Ireland’s soccer association said it was paid after a controversial hand ball by France’s Thierry Henry prevented Ireland from qualifying for the 2010 World Cup.
lead_paragraph: The chief executive of Ireland’s soccer association said Thursday that FIFA had quietly paid compensation to his federation after a controversial hand ball by France’s Thierry Henry prevented Ireland from qualifying for the 2010 World Cup.

abstract: It wasn’t just the amendments that followed the fighting. The war changed the very way Americans relate to their government.
snippet: It wasn’t just the amendments that followed the fighting. The war changed the very way Americans relate to their government.
lead_paragraph: The most obvious constitutional result of the Civil War was the adoption of three landmark constitutional amendments. The 13th ended slavery forever in the United States, while the 14th made all persons born in the United States (including the former slaves) citizens of the nation and prohibited the states from denying anyone the privileges and immunities of American citizenship, due process or law, or equal protection of the law. Finally, the 15th Amendment, ratified in 1870, prohibited the states from denying the franchise to anyone based on “race, color, or previous condition of servitude.”

abstract: A White House-ordered review is expected to produce recommendations such as a new interdepartmental “fusion cell” for recovering American captives, but not a shift in the government’s stance against ransom payments.
snippet: A White House-ordered review is expected to produce recommendations such as a new interdepartmental “fusion cell” for recovering American captives, but not a shift in the government’s stance against ransom payments.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — When President Obama met recently with the mother of James Foley, the American hostage beheaded last August by the Islamic State, she said, he told her that freeing her son and the other American hostages held with him had been his top priority.
